data.meta_description: Lane College, located in Jackson, Tennessee on approximately 55 acres, is a small, private, co-educational, church-related institution that provides a liberal arts curriculum leading to baccalaureate degrees in the Arts and Sciences.
data.text:
Billy Rivera

Billy Rivera is a junior computer science major at Lane College. He resides in Memphis, Tennessee. Currently, he serves as the President of Lane's Computer Science Club, which was created to serve as a support system for students studying computer science at Lane College. Rivera is also a former member of R.O.T.C.

Lashelle Moss

Lashelle Moss was born and raised in Memphis but she resides in Jackson, Mississippi. Currently, she is a senior Sociology major at Lane College and plans to become a social worker. Lashelle serves as the President of Lane's Social Sciences Club and she is a member of Zeta Phi Beta Sorority Inc. Ms. Moss is excited about becoming a Green for All College Ambassador because she wants to make a change at her school and in the surrounding community.
